name: Block Printing on Fabric Workshop
description: Tuesday, January 14th 6 - 9PM Each month we're offering a specialty workshop and bringing in folks who are experts at their craft! This month it's Jenny Nelson of Home Sweet by Hand. Jenny prints beautiful, graphic block-printed fabric and yardage. Join us on Tuesday, January 14th from 6-9PM for this hands-on intensive. The workshop will focus on printing techniques that can be done at home using no specialty machinery. We will be printing on tea-towels, but participants may bring their own napkins, pillow cases, table-runners, or other items to print on as time allows. If you have any questions, please contact us at print@baltimoreprintstudios.com. Tickets are non-refundable.

name: Intro to Letterpress Workshop
description: Sunday, January 12th 11AM - 5PM Our one-day, hands-on letterpress workshop covers all the basics of letterpress printing. Attendees will learn how letterpress printing works,Â how to hand-set wood- and metal-type, print from type and polymer plates, and how to troubleshoot printing and press issues. Students will leave the class understanding how to operate the presses safely and efficiently. This class will provide you the skills to return and rent time to print your own work during our regular studio hours. If you have any questions, please contact us at print@baltimoreprintstudios.com. Unfortunately the web-store cannot handle gift certificates at this time, however we'll still accept them. Please pay in full, email us with your gift certificate number, and we'll reimburse you asap. Sorry for the inconvenience. If this workshop has sold out, please check back! We'll open up next month's soon. Tickets are non-refundable.

name: Intro to Screenprinting Workshop
description: Sunday, January 26th 11AM - 5PM Our one-day, hands-on screenprinting workshop covers all the basics of screenprinting. Attendees will learn first hand how to properly coat, expose, print from, and clean a silkscreen. Differences in inks, printing substrates, screen mesh, and filmwork will all be discussed, and various multi-color registration techniques will be covered. This class will provide you the skills to return and rent time to print your own work during our regular studio hours. name: Baltimore Beer Week
description: Our poster for the 2011 Beerweek features the American Brewery building, built in Baltimore in 1887. The building ceased its beer production in the 1970s, and the building now houses a non-profit. But we preferred to imagine it as it used to be. We designed our poster showcasing the production of beer, from grain being poured in, to beer being pumped out. The poster is a 2-color print, and all black-portions are layered blue over red, all hand printed on French Smart White 110lb Cover, and measures 18x24". Read a little more about the project here.
